1
00:00:12,599 --> 00:00:17,599
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:24,074 --> 00:00:27,870
This is Fairytale Island.

3
00:00:27,911 --> 00:00:34,126
A magical land of princes and princess,
and witches and monsters.

4
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:39,089
Here - accidents from strange events
happen all the time.

5
00:00:39,131 --> 00:00:46,346
That's when people call us - The Fearless 7 -
the greatest heroes on Fairytale Island.

6
00:00:46,388 --> 00:00:49,349
Especially ME - Merlin.

7
00:00:49,391 --> 00:00:56,481
But everything changed the day we defeated
a dragon and saved a princess.

8
00:00:56,523 --> 00:01:01,361
We thought we'd saved a witch -
so we attacked her.

9
00:01:01,403 --> 00:01:08,243
But we were wrong. She wasn't a witch --
she was a princess.

10
00:01:08,285 --> 00:01:10,704
The FAIRY princess!

11
00:01:10,746 --> 00:01:12,164
How were we supposed to know?

12
00:01:12,205 --> 00:01:17,711
She looked like a witch, and everyone knows
that a princess doesn't look like a witch.

13
00:01:17,753 --> 00:01:22,549
Anyways, she wanted to teach us a lesson.
So, she put a curse on us.

14
00:01:22,591 --> 00:01:24,509
And this was a nasty one,

15
00:01:24,552 --> 00:01:29,181
that turned us into ugly little green monsters
whenever people looked at us.

16
00:01:29,222 --> 00:01:35,395
And the only way to break the curse is to get
a kiss from the most beautiful woman in the world.

17
00:01:35,437 --> 00:01:37,522
Are you kidding me?

18
00:01:37,565 --> 00:01:39,567
With this face?

19
00:02:25,696 --> 00:02:27,948
Hello, your majesty.

20
00:02:28,031 --> 00:02:29,282
Good morning ma'am.

21
00:02:29,324 --> 00:02:30,701
Good morning.

22
00:02:34,622 --> 00:02:44,965
Magic tree, magic tree let this morning be the time
that you perform your duty...

23
00:02:50,596 --> 00:02:59,187
...Of bringing me the shoes of youthful,
eternal beauty.

24
00:03:06,737 --> 00:03:07,696
Yes.

25
00:03:07,738 --> 00:03:08,989
WOW!

26
00:03:09,031 --> 00:03:14,578
Change me... Finally.

27
00:03:19,499 --> 00:03:21,627
Not again! How long must I wait?!

28
00:03:21,669 --> 00:03:22,085
Oh No.

29
00:03:22,127 --> 00:03:23,712
Clear these away!

30
00:03:23,754 --> 00:03:25,255
Oh head down.

31
00:03:25,338 --> 00:03:26,882
Oh, pull yourself together.

32
00:03:30,678 --> 00:03:31,804
Here you are.

33
00:03:32,429 --> 00:03:34,557
Oh! Thanks!

34
00:03:56,704 --> 00:03:59,414
Huh? That wasn't here before.

35
00:03:59,456 --> 00:04:01,083
What is she up to now?

36
00:04:42,791 --> 00:04:43,500
Huh?

37
00:04:47,504 --> 00:04:49,047
You weren't here before.

38
00:04:53,802 --> 00:04:54,427
Whatever.

39
00:04:59,349 --> 00:05:00,183
Owe!

40
00:05:04,688 --> 00:05:05,480
Yes!

41
00:05:08,609 --> 00:05:13,321
I can't believe my beloved daughter
Snow White has turned eighteen.

42
00:05:13,405 --> 00:05:19,995
I only wish her mother could see the kind of smart
and beautiful young woman she's become.

43
00:05:20,037 --> 00:05:22,873
Strange thing happened during the party.

44
00:05:22,915 --> 00:05:26,669
The castle guards brought in a woman -
named Regina.

45
00:05:26,710 --> 00:05:32,299
They said she was a witch.
But she was too beautiful to be a witch.

46
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:37,429
I have married Regina,
Everything feels so perfect!

47
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:44,269
...Except for Regina's strange looking mirror.
There's something not quite right.

48
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:49,232
People around the castle
have been disappearing one by one.

49
00:05:49,274 --> 00:05:52,152
Is it because of that peculiar mirror?

50
00:05:52,194 --> 00:05:54,404
I saw it with my own eyes!

51
00:05:54,446 --> 00:05:57,240
Regina - talking to a tree!

52
00:05:57,282 --> 00:05:59,451
She must be a witch!

53
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:03,622
I should send Snow away, to a safer place.

54
00:06:03,706 --> 00:06:04,915
My dear Snow

55
00:06:04,957 --> 00:06:08,919
by the time you read this,
my fate will be uncertain.

56
00:06:08,961 --> 00:06:11,213
She's coming for me now.

57
00:06:11,254 --> 00:06:15,508
I only hope you can find The Fearless Seven
and ask them for help!

58
00:06:17,219 --> 00:06:22,099
Apples... the most suspicious of fruits.

59
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:28,146
Oh, papa, where are you.

60
00:06:31,066 --> 00:06:32,693
But they don't look dangerous.

61
00:06:49,752 --> 00:06:50,252
Regina?

62
00:06:50,293 --> 00:06:54,882
No!! My shoes! Get her!

63
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,765
Owe!

64
00:07:02,806 --> 00:07:03,849
Can I borrow this?

65
00:07:03,891 --> 00:07:04,391
Okay.

66
00:07:04,474 --> 00:07:05,350
Thanks!

67
00:07:19,948 --> 00:07:20,824
What?

68
00:07:22,284 --> 00:07:24,161
No!

69
00:07:32,169 --> 00:07:34,880
Short, chubby and green.

70
00:07:36,006 --> 00:07:37,966
Green is like an ogre.

71
00:07:38,008 --> 00:07:40,969
Blue or yellow could have
made us look cute and cuddly.

72
00:07:41,011 --> 00:07:43,722
Quit your complaining, Merlin.

73
00:07:43,806 --> 00:07:47,976
I'm figuring out how to take this curse
and kick it where the sun don't shine.

74
00:07:48,018 --> 00:07:52,439
Listen, we need to find the most
beautifulest princess to kiss us,

75
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,650
and we've just about run out of options!

76
00:07:54,692 --> 00:07:59,112
How would a beautiful woman even see you,
Mr. Invisible?

77
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,492
What was that? Some kind of bird?

78
00:08:08,789 --> 00:08:15,462
Magic Mirror full of wisdom,
who's the fairest in the kingdom??

79
00:08:15,503 --> 00:08:18,465
The woman who wears the red shoes.

80
00:08:20,008 --> 00:08:23,554
And side-note: "wisdom" and "kingdom"
don't really rhyme.

81
00:08:23,596 --> 00:08:27,140
Cut the sass and tell me her name!

82
00:08:27,182 --> 00:08:27,975
Ha!

83
00:08:28,016 --> 00:08:30,102
How should I know? I don't get out much.

84
00:08:30,143 --> 00:08:32,520
Well, you are the magic mirror.

85
00:08:32,563 --> 00:08:37,275
"Magic" is just my first name.
It's short for "Magitchard," like Richard.

86
00:08:37,317 --> 00:08:39,903
What can you do then?

87
00:08:39,945 --> 00:08:44,074
I just reflect what I see.
The truth. And the truth is,

88
00:08:44,116 --> 00:08:48,829
that you should see yourself right now.

89
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:51,538
Watch it.

90
00:08:52,289 --> 00:08:58,881
Distribute wanted posters to every town, village,
valley, forest and forge in the kingdom and find her!

91
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:06,346
I feel my power draining. I don't have much time.
The aging is accelerating.

92
00:09:06,429 --> 00:09:10,225
And only three bumbling bits of kindling for help.

93
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:14,354
Perhaps you should recruit another.
Someone who stands to gain from your success.

94
00:09:14,396 --> 00:09:16,189
How about this fellow?

95
00:09:17,107 --> 00:09:23,656
Interesting. Tell me more, Magitchard.

96
00:09:24,948 --> 00:09:27,242
Hey, hey, over here, over here!

97
00:09:27,284 --> 00:09:28,702
Si', si' come, very quick!

98
00:09:28,744 --> 00:09:31,121
Look at us! Look, look, look!

99
00:09:31,163 --> 00:09:32,080
What is it?

100
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:39,046
I know a lot about silhouettes.

101
00:09:39,087 --> 00:09:41,256
And I think this shape... is a witch.

102
00:09:41,339 --> 00:09:43,175
Let's not jump to conclusions.

103
00:09:43,216 --> 00:09:47,012
Yes, it could be a witch, or -- yah, it's a witch.

104
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:48,847
The witch who cursed us!

105
00:09:48,931 --> 00:09:51,099
Let's catch her and make her break the spell!

106
00:10:09,827 --> 00:10:10,285
En garde!

107
00:10:10,327 --> 00:10:12,370
Wands where I can see 'em, witch!

108
00:10:21,504 --> 00:10:22,172
Fraulein!

109
00:10:22,214 --> 00:10:23,381
NO, NO, NO, Stop!

110
00:10:23,465 --> 00:10:28,470
I baked you some revenge!

111
00:10:29,555 --> 00:10:30,931
beautiful.

112
00:10:30,973 --> 00:10:33,726
I didn't know anyone could be so beautiful.

113
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:35,185
How did she end up with us?

114
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:46,822
Hello, dear lady.
Welcome to my home-slash-command post.

115
00:10:46,864 --> 00:10:49,199
I have six roommates, but my name's on the lease.

116
00:10:49,241 --> 00:10:50,868
I pay the rent.

117
00:10:50,909 --> 00:10:55,288
YOUR home? Oh my gosh, I am, I am so sorry. I was,

118
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:57,249
I was starving and I wandered into this home --

119
00:10:57,332 --> 00:11:02,004
There's no need to apologize.
We didn't mean to interrupt your stolen meal.

120
00:11:02,045 --> 00:11:05,173
If you're still hungry,
I can whip up something simple --

121
00:11:05,215 --> 00:11:07,384
You see,
I marinate the celery root in a mustard aioli--

122
00:11:07,425 --> 00:11:08,468
Who is that?

123
00:11:10,303 --> 00:11:12,305
Ahh-who?

124
00:11:17,269 --> 00:11:22,107
Wow! I look so...different.

125
00:11:22,149 --> 00:11:27,237
I mean my face, and my waist. My waist? My waist.

126
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:29,907
Oh my gosh! What happened to me?

127
00:11:31,909 --> 00:11:34,452
Well...

128
00:11:34,494 --> 00:11:40,500
Ha! Must have gotten up so quickly.
My back is killing me!

129
00:11:40,542 --> 00:11:43,420
You mean your head, right? Do you need help?

130
00:11:43,461 --> 00:11:46,464
No. I'm fine.

131
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:54,347
Um, is that really what I look like?
In the mirror. Do you see the same thing?

132
00:11:54,389 --> 00:11:55,891
You're beautiful, miss.

133
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,810
Like an angel?

134
00:11:57,851 --> 00:12:00,062
Wow, really?

135
00:12:00,103 --> 00:12:01,063
Could it be...?

136
00:12:01,146 --> 00:12:03,440
Excuse me, but who are you?

137
00:12:03,481 --> 00:12:04,733
Oh, I'm Sno--

138
00:12:04,775 --> 00:12:06,026
"Snot"?

139
00:12:06,109 --> 00:12:08,737
No, no, no, no, no, no.

140
00:12:08,779 --> 00:12:14,451
My name is... Red Shoes.

141
00:12:14,492 --> 00:12:17,287
Yep, it's me, Red Shoes!

142
00:12:17,329 --> 00:12:21,917
Cool name.
By any chance would that be "Princess" Red Shoes?

143
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:26,504
Of course she's a princess!
How could she be so beautiful if she weren't?

144
00:12:26,546 --> 00:12:28,841
Obviously! Right, miss?

145
00:12:28,882 --> 00:12:34,179
Obviously...I mean, I am a princess...
Who are you guys?

146
00:12:34,221 --> 00:12:39,602
I'm Merlin, part time hero, full time romantic.

147
00:12:39,643 --> 00:12:42,980
And this is Jack, Hans,
Arthur, Pino, Noki, and Kio.

148
00:12:43,021 --> 00:12:46,609
No way! Your names are the same as F7!

149
00:12:46,650 --> 00:12:49,653
The Fearless Seven. I'm looking for them!

150
00:12:49,695 --> 00:12:53,073
Let me guess, Merlin's your favorite.

151
00:12:53,115 --> 00:12:55,200
No, not really.

152
00:12:55,242 --> 00:12:57,535
Nah, that Merlin's not your type.

153
00:12:57,578 --> 00:13:00,748
You seem like a Prince Arthur fan to me.

154
00:13:00,789 --> 00:13:03,917
Honestly, none of them are really my type.

155
00:13:06,503 --> 00:13:12,425
Oh. Well, that's fine because we're not them,
we're actually completely different people.

156
00:13:12,467 --> 00:13:17,180
In no way are we the same guys put under a curse
and changed into different forms,

157
00:13:17,222 --> 00:13:20,225
but only if someone looks at us,
it's very complicated..

158
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:22,352
Glad we're all clear.

159
00:13:22,394 --> 00:13:25,438
So how can I assist you, my fair lady?

160
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:29,652
I need to find my father.
And I know that the F7 can help...

161
00:13:29,693 --> 00:13:34,322
We know the F7 very well,
and their schedule is fully booked.

162
00:13:34,364 --> 00:13:37,075
Leave it to me!
I'll find your father within the month.

163
00:13:37,117 --> 00:13:38,619
I can do it in one week.

164
00:13:38,661 --> 00:13:39,828
Four days.

165
00:13:39,870 --> 00:13:40,537
Three!

166
00:13:40,579 --> 00:13:40,996
Two!

167
00:13:41,038 --> 00:13:41,914
One!

168
00:13:41,955 --> 00:13:42,873
--and a half.

169
00:13:42,915 --> 00:13:45,083
I already found your father like two weeks ago.

170
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:46,251
Really?

171
00:13:46,293 --> 00:13:49,212
I just need a few days
to get him across state lines.

172
00:13:49,254 --> 00:13:51,339
I seriously need to find my dad.

173
00:13:51,381 --> 00:13:55,594
Hold on.
Nobody has seen the F7 in over a year, right?

174
00:13:55,678 --> 00:13:57,470
You're not going to find them now.

175
00:13:57,512 --> 00:13:59,264
We're your best bet.

176
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:04,770
Wow. No one's offered to help me
for such a long time.

177
00:14:04,812 --> 00:14:05,896
You guys are awesome.

178
00:14:05,938 --> 00:14:09,441
Really? You think... we're awesome?

179
00:14:09,524 --> 00:14:14,988
Yeah, you guys are caring, and sweet, and...

180
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:17,700
...And not completely hideous to look at?

181
00:14:17,741 --> 00:14:21,161
No. You guys are totally adorable.

182
00:14:21,203 --> 00:14:22,955
I think I hit her too hard.

183
00:14:22,996 --> 00:14:25,373
But she is a beautiful

184
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,336
She can help me break the curse.

185
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:37,845
Who is coming to my birthday party?

186
00:14:37,886 --> 00:14:39,638
Has Ariel rsvp'ed?

187
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:42,474
She says she can't make it, sir.
She has to wax her legs.

188
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:43,642
But she's a mermaid!

189
00:14:43,684 --> 00:14:45,185
What about Sleeping Beauty?

190
00:14:45,227 --> 00:14:46,311
Doctor's appointment.

191
00:14:46,353 --> 00:14:47,229
Is she sick?

192
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:48,438
Says she has insomnia.

193
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,733
If she's not going to sleep,
she can come to our party.

194
00:14:50,774 --> 00:14:55,070
What about Rapunzel?
And don't tell me she's getting her hair done.

195
00:14:55,112 --> 00:14:58,281
No, she's writing something called... a book.

196
00:14:58,323 --> 00:14:59,407
Princess Cruise?

197
00:14:59,449 --> 00:15:00,533
That's a ship, sir.

198
00:15:00,576 --> 00:15:01,243
Princess Leia?

199
00:15:01,284 --> 00:15:02,327
She's a general now.

200
00:15:02,369 --> 00:15:05,080
I demand glorious guests!

201
00:15:05,122 --> 00:15:08,667
I couldn't be any more unpopular.

202
00:15:08,709 --> 00:15:11,294
And I don't understand why.

203
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:16,424
Greetings, Prince Average.

204
00:15:16,466 --> 00:15:19,136
It's pronounced "AVE-VOO-RAHJ."

205
00:15:19,177 --> 00:15:21,054
Sure it is.

206
00:15:21,096 --> 00:15:24,516
If you're here
for the We Love Our Peasants Gruel Giveaway,

207
00:15:24,558 --> 00:15:27,352
that promotion has ended.
Grab your wrinkles and go.

208
00:15:27,435 --> 00:15:28,186
Move along.

209
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,444
Do you think the people would respect you

210
00:15:36,486 --> 00:15:43,702
if you celebrated your birthday
with a beautiful woman on your arm.

211
00:15:43,744 --> 00:15:48,832
Finally, someone talking sense!
This horrible crone gets it.

212
00:15:48,874 --> 00:15:51,835
Then may I suggest inviting...

213
00:15:51,877 --> 00:15:54,046
...this young lady.

214
00:15:54,797 --> 00:15:57,925
She's beautiful! When can she get here?

215
00:15:57,966 --> 00:16:03,471
Well that's up to you.
You see, she's stolen something from me.

216
00:16:03,513 --> 00:16:09,394
You find her, bring her along with you
and you won't look like such a loser,

217
00:16:09,436 --> 00:16:13,106
and I get my shoes back.

218
00:16:13,148 --> 00:16:15,067
Fear not, loyal hag.

219
00:16:15,108 --> 00:16:21,198
I, Prince Ave- voo-rahj, shall find this fugitive
and make her pay for her crimes.

220
00:16:21,239 --> 00:16:24,409
By making her attend my birthday party!

221
00:16:24,451 --> 00:16:27,079
There shall be balloons!

222
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:30,833
I just thought of that!
Let's have a lot of balloons!

223
00:16:30,874 --> 00:16:34,712
More like buffoons.

224
00:16:41,134 --> 00:16:43,053
It looks just like papa.

225
00:16:48,809 --> 00:16:50,268
Papa won't recognize me.

226
00:16:54,064 --> 00:17:01,029
Huh? Why won't these shoes just, just come off?

227
00:17:06,619 --> 00:17:10,288
Oh, yes. This is me.

228
00:17:18,589 --> 00:17:22,092
Would you like to join me in a moisturizing mask?

229
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:28,348
Oh, thanks. Oh, oof, but I am so tired.

230
00:17:28,389 --> 00:17:32,686
Are you sure?
It's very important to take care of your skin.

231
00:17:32,728 --> 00:17:33,436
Positive.

232
00:17:35,521 --> 00:17:39,401
but this is the finest French recipe meant
to hydrate skin.

233
00:17:39,484 --> 00:17:41,862
It is made of French poopie!

234
00:17:42,988 --> 00:17:44,031
Papa?!

235
00:17:45,783 --> 00:17:50,120
A spell that makes you fall in love...

236
00:17:50,162 --> 00:17:51,747
Ah. There it is.

237
00:17:51,789 --> 00:17:54,166
Merlin, have you seen my cookbook?

238
00:17:54,207 --> 00:17:56,459
Have you checked in the kitchen?

239
00:17:56,501 --> 00:18:00,213
Ah, silly me. The kitchen. Of course.

240
00:18:02,215 --> 00:18:05,177
Now. Where was I?

241
00:18:05,218 --> 00:18:09,640
Merlin. Have you seen my moisturizer?
It's nowhere to be found...

242
00:18:09,682 --> 00:18:13,561
No. Whatever it is. I haven't seen it.
Now please - go away.

243
00:18:13,602 --> 00:18:15,729
Someone's got anger management issues.

244
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:22,152
Getting a kiss was never a problem with this face.

245
00:18:25,030 --> 00:18:25,948
Red Shoes?

246
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:33,581
Papa? Papa, are you there? Papa!

247
00:18:56,687 --> 00:19:01,441
Boys, I'm telling you,
sweet treats are the way to a woman's heart.

248
00:19:03,526 --> 00:19:06,697
It works. I call it an auto- portrait!

249
00:19:06,739 --> 00:19:08,365
I call it, the dupli-cata-tron!

250
00:19:08,406 --> 00:19:09,825
I call it, selfie!

251
00:19:09,867 --> 00:19:11,744
Red Shoes must love it!

252
00:19:11,785 --> 00:19:15,706
Monsieur, Monsieur.
She doesn't want sweets and selfies.

253
00:19:15,748 --> 00:19:16,790
Women want...

254
00:19:16,832 --> 00:19:18,208
...diamonds.

255
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:19,001
Merlin?

256
00:19:25,841 --> 00:19:29,678
"The Book of Spells to Make You Fall in Love?"

257
00:19:32,389 --> 00:19:33,431
Huh?

258
00:19:33,473 --> 00:19:37,519
Okay, big, terrifying wooden bunny.

259
00:19:37,561 --> 00:19:38,520
You're a nice bunny.

260
00:19:38,687 --> 00:19:41,940
You're a vegan bunny, right?

261
00:19:45,277 --> 00:19:47,821
What... was that?... Lightning?

262
00:19:47,863 --> 00:19:49,865
Actually, it's called magic.

263
00:19:49,907 --> 00:19:50,532
I do it.

264
00:19:50,574 --> 00:19:52,826
Really?... Then... do some!

265
00:20:13,556 --> 00:20:16,474
Keep running! And whatever you do,
don't look back!

266
00:20:16,516 --> 00:20:17,601
But I can't leave without you -

267
00:20:17,685 --> 00:20:20,437
You're looking back! Don't do that!

268
00:20:20,478 --> 00:20:22,105
But...

269
00:20:22,147 --> 00:20:26,652
Hate to zap you, long ears.
But I gotta impress a beautiful woman.

270
00:20:26,694 --> 00:20:29,029
Big, scary bunny! Over here!

271
00:20:29,071 --> 00:20:31,073
Red, stop putting yourself in--!

272
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,952
Danger...

273
00:20:54,763 --> 00:20:56,724
Arthur! I got you!

274
00:20:56,765 --> 00:21:02,896
It's no use, Red Shoes.
I'm slipping away. Not much time.

275
00:21:02,938 --> 00:21:06,066
Just... need to... use that core of mine...

276
00:21:06,108 --> 00:21:08,569
I see that light at the end of the funnel.

277
00:21:08,611 --> 00:21:14,324
Time for me to kick butt in heaven.
I had a good run. Hashtag blessed.

278
00:21:14,366 --> 00:21:18,286
Oh I used to be able to bench 250...

279
00:21:18,328 --> 00:21:21,749
Before I go, how about a farewell kiss?

280
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:24,793
Red Shoes! Oh, thank goodness you're safe.

281
00:21:24,877 --> 00:21:26,169
Do you need CPR?

282
00:21:26,211 --> 00:21:29,923
I'm basically an expert.
And don't worry, I brushed my teeth. Twice.

283
00:21:29,965 --> 00:21:32,217
No, no-no-no, I'm fine, but Arthur - he's stuck.

284
00:21:32,259 --> 00:21:33,927
He tried to save me,
and then he got stuck underneath...

285
00:21:33,969 --> 00:21:35,638
Would you get up.

286
00:21:35,679 --> 00:21:37,389
What? He's not hurt?

287
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:38,557
Only his pride.

288
00:21:38,599 --> 00:21:42,352
Seriously, Arthur.
You need to find a better way to hit on girls.

289
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:54,990
Stand back. I may have to risk my life again.

290
00:22:03,791 --> 00:22:05,918
Someone call for three inventors?

291
00:22:05,959 --> 00:22:07,502
For three geniuses?

292
00:22:07,544 --> 00:22:09,421
Ooh! That sounds like us!

293
00:22:10,964 --> 00:22:12,382
Everyone came running to help.

294
00:22:12,424 --> 00:22:14,092
Great...just great.

295
00:22:14,176 --> 00:22:16,178
Everyone except Merlin that is.

296
00:22:16,219 --> 00:22:18,764
Ah. Super. There he is now.

297
00:22:18,806 --> 00:22:19,807
Where have you been?

298
00:22:19,848 --> 00:22:22,810
Something awful could have happened
to Red if I hadn't shown up.

299
00:22:22,851 --> 00:22:30,233
You?! Don't even... go there... I saved... her first.

300
00:22:30,317 --> 00:22:31,109
Right?

301
00:22:31,151 --> 00:22:32,360
I was worried about you.

302
00:22:32,402 --> 00:22:36,114
I was worried about me too. But mostly you.

303
00:22:36,156 --> 00:22:39,993
No one needs to worry.
Arthur's here. Please, my lady.

304
00:22:40,035 --> 00:22:41,161
Um... OK

305
00:22:50,629 --> 00:22:52,881
You shouldn't go into the forest by yourself.

306
00:22:52,923 --> 00:22:58,095
It's a nightmarish landscape fit only
for bloodthirsty warriors like myself.

307
00:22:58,136 --> 00:22:59,471
And squirrels.

308
00:22:59,512 --> 00:23:01,807
I thought I saw my father.

309
00:23:01,890 --> 00:23:04,517
Turned out just to be that big bunny.

310
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:08,897
Well, if you ever make such a dangerous
and weird mistake again,

311
00:23:08,939 --> 00:23:11,274
just know that I can protect you.

312
00:23:11,316 --> 00:23:13,068
That's very kind.

313
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:17,740
And if you really want
to express your gratitude, you can...

314
00:23:19,658 --> 00:23:27,374
Oh, I am so sorry!
That was much... slapper than I intended it to be.

315
00:23:27,415 --> 00:23:32,880
Oh, it happens. No problem.
Maybe an apology kiss then?

316
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:37,551
Bravo, mon ami!

317
00:23:37,593 --> 00:23:39,637
Nice try.

318
00:23:39,678 --> 00:23:41,263
Red Shoes!

319
00:23:45,559 --> 00:23:49,271
Gentlemen, to break this curse we're going
to have to work as a tightly-knit team.

320
00:23:49,312 --> 00:23:51,356
Which means you do everything I say.

321
00:23:51,439 --> 00:23:52,065
Excuse me?

322
00:23:52,107 --> 00:23:52,524
Huh?

323
00:23:52,566 --> 00:23:52,983
What? No.

324
00:23:53,025 --> 00:23:53,942
You got to be kidding

325
00:23:54,026 --> 00:23:56,236
Hans and Jack will search around the dismal lake.

326
00:23:56,278 --> 00:23:58,989
Triplets, you search the caves of despair.

327
00:23:59,031 --> 00:24:02,200
Red Shoes and I will go to Golden Goose Avenue.

328
00:24:02,242 --> 00:24:07,080
Golden Goose Avenue.
Which happens to be your go-to place for dates.

329
00:24:07,122 --> 00:24:12,210
We are going to focus on the mission.
And then see where the evening takes us.

330
00:24:12,252 --> 00:24:16,339
The only thing you're going to shop
for on Golden Goose Avenue is rejection.

331
00:24:16,381 --> 00:24:18,091
And you can't even afford that.

332
00:24:18,133 --> 00:24:20,594
I like my odds. You saw what she did.

333
00:24:20,636 --> 00:24:25,140
An expression of affection.
Every woman shows it differently.

334
00:24:25,182 --> 00:24:26,850
You took your shot, you got slapped.

335
00:24:26,892 --> 00:24:32,565
May I remind you that this is the closest thing
to a kiss anyone's had since the curse.

336
00:24:32,606 --> 00:24:36,526
Let's work together
to guide Red Shoes' feelings towards me,

337
00:24:36,569 --> 00:24:38,486
so We can break the curse.

338
00:24:38,528 --> 00:24:39,655
What about the rest of us?

339
00:24:39,697 --> 00:24:44,577
After I resume my princely form,
the word about F7 will be out.

340
00:24:44,618 --> 00:24:48,538
Ladies will be begging to kiss your green mugs.

341
00:24:48,581 --> 00:24:49,289
Really?

342
00:24:49,331 --> 00:24:50,498
Sounds reasonable.

343
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:52,167
I'll bring the gelato!

344
00:24:52,209 --> 00:24:54,753
Getting one kiss sure is easier than getting seven.

345
00:24:54,795 --> 00:24:57,590
This is not a plan! He's just out for himself.

346
00:24:57,631 --> 00:24:59,633
A half-baked plan is better than none.

347
00:24:59,675 --> 00:25:03,386
Don't worry, Merlin.
I have a big assignment for you.

348
00:25:03,428 --> 00:25:05,931
Hmph. Big Assignment?

349
00:25:05,973 --> 00:25:08,266
Here you go. I drew this up last night.

350
00:25:08,308 --> 00:25:14,189
I can't tell if this drawing is terrible
or really avant-garde.

351
00:25:14,231 --> 00:25:18,193
Awe, my neighbor's a great art teacher,
Pablo Picass-ogre.

352
00:25:18,235 --> 00:25:22,114
One thing's for sure, Daddy's on the big side

353
00:25:22,197 --> 00:25:24,825
...of big.

354
00:25:24,867 --> 00:25:26,577
You must take after your mother.

355
00:25:26,619 --> 00:25:28,120
No, I look a lot like pap--

356
00:25:28,161 --> 00:25:35,878
Oh, yeah, my mother. Gosh, we, exactly. Twins.

357
00:25:35,919 --> 00:25:37,880
Alright, you know the plan.

358
00:25:37,921 --> 00:25:40,173
Let's move! Deploy!

359
00:25:40,215 --> 00:25:42,009
Thunder dwarfs are go!

360
00:25:44,219 --> 00:25:45,929
And where do you think you're going?

361
00:25:45,971 --> 00:25:47,890
Your post is right there.

362
00:25:47,931 --> 00:25:49,474
You watch the savage monster.

363
00:25:49,516 --> 00:25:50,517
I call him vicious.

364
00:25:50,559 --> 00:25:52,185
I call him "Woodbottom."

365
00:25:52,227 --> 00:25:54,813
Don't worry, Merlin,
we'll make sure you get kissed, too.

366
00:25:54,855 --> 00:25:56,231
Eventually.

367
00:25:57,566 --> 00:25:59,026
we will split up here.

368
00:25:59,067 --> 00:26:00,360
Alright. See you later.

369
00:26:01,695 --> 00:26:04,615
I know exactly where we should look
to find your father!

370
00:26:04,657 --> 00:26:06,158
Really? Where?

371
00:26:14,207 --> 00:26:15,417
Daddy!

372
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,502
Wow!

373
00:26:17,544 --> 00:26:18,921
Is this what I think it is?

374
00:26:18,962 --> 00:26:25,135
I present Excalibur, a legendary sword trapped
in this rock for centuries,

375
00:26:25,177 --> 00:26:28,764
waiting for a man of great strength to release it.

376
00:26:28,806 --> 00:26:32,059
It says: "Do not attempt to remove by force."

377
00:26:32,142 --> 00:26:34,853
Oh, right. I guess, uh,

378
00:26:34,895 --> 00:26:41,276
the truth is, I realized you are the woman
of my destiny the first time I saw you.

379
00:26:41,318 --> 00:26:44,029
I thought if I could show you my strength...

380
00:26:44,071 --> 00:26:46,489
...I would be worthy of your affections.

381
00:26:50,452 --> 00:26:53,956
Oh! Oops! I'll put it back.

382
00:26:54,039 --> 00:26:55,749
No! No, no, no. Can I hold it?

383
00:27:06,176 --> 00:27:09,346
Oh, Arthur, it's just beginners luck.

384
00:27:09,387 --> 00:27:11,932
You want me to maybe pull it out for you again?

385
00:27:11,974 --> 00:27:15,060
No. I'm not humiliated at all.

386
00:27:15,102 --> 00:27:16,103
Let's go.

387
00:27:25,613 --> 00:27:29,575
Don't look at me like that.
I'm the real prisoner here.

388
00:27:29,617 --> 00:27:31,910
What? You're hungry?

389
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:34,997
and fetch

390
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:47,718
Hop along, big guy.
There's no way Arthur is breaking this curse alone.

391
00:28:04,484 --> 00:28:05,360
Excuse me!

392
00:28:07,237 --> 00:28:09,072
Arthur, where are you going?

393
00:28:11,617 --> 00:28:13,869
Oh. Okay.

394
00:28:13,952 --> 00:28:15,037
See you later.

395
00:28:16,163 --> 00:28:17,330
Hi.

396
00:28:17,372 --> 00:28:20,292
Oh, look at what you made me do!

397
00:28:20,333 --> 00:28:21,418
You...

398
00:28:21,459 --> 00:28:22,795
I'm sorry.

399
00:28:22,836 --> 00:28:26,423
made me make it perfect. Thank you.

400
00:28:28,884 --> 00:28:30,678
I'm so sorry.

401
00:28:30,719 --> 00:28:36,224
No. Don't be. I'm sorry. Are you all right? And...

402
00:28:36,266 --> 00:28:38,435
don't worry about this.

403
00:28:41,564 --> 00:28:42,230
What?

404
00:28:42,314 --> 00:28:43,941
Ta-da!

405
00:28:46,276 --> 00:28:48,361
Excuse me, have you seen this man?

406
00:29:51,049 --> 00:29:53,969
Arthur. I was thinking.

407
00:29:54,011 --> 00:29:58,849
What if I just like pull out the Excalibur for you?
our secret.

408
00:29:58,891 --> 00:30:01,018
Really? We have a secret now?

409
00:30:01,059 --> 00:30:01,852
Yeah.

410
00:30:01,894 --> 00:30:06,815
I like a girl who can keep things classified.
Let's find your pops, Red!

411
00:30:06,857 --> 00:30:07,691
Bye Guys

412
00:30:12,112 --> 00:30:12,988
What?

413
00:30:14,322 --> 00:30:17,868
Hey, you. ...No.

414
00:30:18,869 --> 00:30:19,327
Hey!

415
00:30:20,621 --> 00:30:21,371
stop!

416
00:30:27,586 --> 00:30:28,420
C'mon!

417
00:30:55,739 --> 00:30:58,200
Oh, you guys don't have to help.

418
00:30:58,241 --> 00:31:00,327
That's not her. C'mon.

419
00:31:00,368 --> 00:31:01,161
Sorry, miss.

420
00:31:05,123 --> 00:31:07,835
Red Shoes! Red Shoes! Where has she gone.

421
00:31:07,876 --> 00:31:09,628
Where's Red Shoes?

422
00:31:09,670 --> 00:31:11,129
That's what I'd like to know!

423
00:31:11,797 --> 00:31:13,340
Wait a minute,

424
00:31:13,381 --> 00:31:14,800
who said you could leave your post?

425
00:31:14,842 --> 00:31:16,802
I'm just walking the bunny.

426
00:31:19,137 --> 00:31:21,890
Red Shoes, where are you?

427
00:31:21,932 --> 00:31:24,059
Hey, you've seen this girl?

428
00:31:29,648 --> 00:31:30,983
Look what I found.

429
00:31:31,024 --> 00:31:34,319
Oh, those are mine. Um,
can I actually have my shoes back?

430
00:31:36,780 --> 00:31:39,491
No way! You're not serious, are you?

431
00:31:39,532 --> 00:31:43,411
I'm really not in the mood.
Could you just please give'em back to me?

432
00:31:43,453 --> 00:31:45,748
Ha! They won't even fit on you!

433
00:31:45,789 --> 00:31:47,833
They're gonna fit me better than they fit you.

434
00:31:47,875 --> 00:31:48,541
Hey!

435
00:31:49,918 --> 00:31:51,211
Red Shoes?

436
00:31:51,253 --> 00:31:52,963
Guys, guys, I'm here!

437
00:31:56,508 --> 00:31:58,093
Red Shoes!

438
00:31:58,135 --> 00:31:59,637
Red Shoes, where are you?

439
00:32:01,013 --> 00:32:03,390
Even the hideous dwarfs won't help you.

440
00:32:06,226 --> 00:32:12,315
Those dwarfs are not hideous,
and I don't need anyone to help me.

441
00:32:12,357 --> 00:32:13,400
Ahh-Owe!

442
00:32:13,441 --> 00:32:18,155
Freeze! Put the shoes down, get on your knees,
and put your hands behind your head.

443
00:32:18,196 --> 00:32:19,865
On second thought - they're yours.

444
00:32:19,907 --> 00:32:22,993
There's no need to push me into a corner.

445
00:32:23,035 --> 00:32:24,578
This is super scary.

446
00:32:35,798 --> 00:32:37,549
Your red shoes, m'lady.

447
00:32:38,341 --> 00:32:39,301
Thank you.

448
00:32:39,342 --> 00:32:42,137
Excuse me miss, have we met?

449
00:32:42,220 --> 00:32:46,058
Umm... well...
that's kind of a complicated question.

450
00:32:46,099 --> 00:32:47,768
Red Shoes?

451
00:32:47,810 --> 00:32:50,771
Gotta go. Be safe.

452
00:32:50,813 --> 00:32:51,313
Umm...

453
00:33:10,958 --> 00:33:11,541
Guys!

454
00:33:14,544 --> 00:33:16,129
Where has she gone?

455
00:33:17,089 --> 00:33:18,173
Red Shoes!

456
00:33:18,882 --> 00:33:19,549
Stop!

457
00:33:22,678 --> 00:33:23,470
Hold on!

458
00:33:27,224 --> 00:33:29,226
Huh, wait a minute.

459
00:33:29,267 --> 00:33:31,687
Gotcha now, don't we?

460
00:33:31,770 --> 00:33:37,234
Ha-ha... I don't get it.

461
00:33:37,275 --> 00:33:40,070
Now we know how fast bunny can hop in a pinch.

462
00:33:40,112 --> 00:33:41,529
Thank you for helping me, Merlin.

463
00:33:41,572 --> 00:33:46,034
Pleasure my lady. But I also did it for us.

464
00:33:46,076 --> 00:33:49,496
By the way, what is this?

465
00:33:49,537 --> 00:33:56,253
Gush it sounds silly,
but it's my shoes. they're magical.

466
00:33:56,294 --> 00:33:59,422
I know they're fabulous,
but why they are after you?

467
00:33:59,464 --> 00:34:03,677
No my shoes, they are... actually made of magic.

468
00:34:03,719 --> 00:34:05,220
Red shoes!

469
00:34:05,303 --> 00:34:06,471
Are you a criminal?

470
00:34:06,513 --> 00:34:08,181
No, of course not.

471
00:34:09,099 --> 00:34:12,394
I know girl this pretty
couldn't possibly be a criminal

472
00:34:12,435 --> 00:34:13,646
Look we should head out now.

473
00:34:13,687 --> 00:34:15,856
There could be more guards around any minute.

474
00:34:15,898 --> 00:34:18,984
Don't worry about them. I've got these bad boys.

475
00:34:19,026 --> 00:34:22,487
This is going to make so much harder
to find my dad.

476
00:34:26,158 --> 00:34:27,325
I have an idea!

477
00:35:11,536 --> 00:35:12,495
What do you think?

478
00:35:12,955 --> 00:35:18,126
That is amazing. Thank you.

479
00:35:35,227 --> 00:35:38,230
You had a thing on your cheek

480
00:35:38,271 --> 00:35:39,356
Alright, let's go.

481
00:35:58,792 --> 00:36:00,210
We've been walking for hours.

482
00:36:00,252 --> 00:36:02,462
And we'll keep walking till we find her.

483
00:36:09,469 --> 00:36:12,347
Now we've got her

484
00:36:12,389 --> 00:36:14,016
Are they gone?

485
00:36:14,057 --> 00:36:14,975
Who cares.

486
00:36:15,017 --> 00:36:16,727
Com'n let's go see.

487
00:36:17,728 --> 00:36:18,478
look at that!

488
00:36:19,396 --> 00:36:20,773
Wow!

489
00:36:20,814 --> 00:36:21,857
awesome

490
00:36:21,899 --> 00:36:22,858
Who's that?

491
00:36:22,941 --> 00:36:24,276
It's the girl's father.

492
00:36:24,317 --> 00:36:25,736
But where is the girl?

493
00:36:25,778 --> 00:36:28,906
It saids to go to risky rock,
so she must be there.

494
00:36:28,947 --> 00:36:30,532
But why risky rock?

495
00:36:30,574 --> 00:36:32,117
We should ask the girl.

496
00:36:32,159 --> 00:36:34,494
Perfect! Where is the girl?

497
00:36:34,536 --> 00:36:38,081
It saids to go to risky rock,
so she must be there.

498
00:36:38,123 --> 00:36:40,793
But why risky rock?

499
00:36:40,834 --> 00:36:42,210
We should ask the girl.

500
00:36:42,252 --> 00:36:44,337
Um... where is the girl?

501
00:36:44,379 --> 00:36:46,965
It saids to go to risky rock,
so she must be there.

502
00:36:47,007 --> 00:36:49,176
But why risky rock?

503
00:36:49,217 --> 00:36:50,678
We should ask the girl.

504
00:37:10,488 --> 00:37:13,241
Owe! What was that for?

505
00:37:13,283 --> 00:37:16,286
You, sir, are sabotaging my relationship
with Red Shoes.

506
00:37:16,328 --> 00:37:18,413
What "relationship" are you talking about?

507
00:37:18,455 --> 00:37:22,417
Red Shoes and I share a secret.
I would tell you what it is.

508
00:37:22,459 --> 00:37:24,294
But it's a secret.

509
00:37:24,336 --> 00:37:27,464
Well, while you're busy keeping secrets,
I'm going to break my curse.

510
00:37:27,547 --> 00:37:29,800
You're nothing without your spells, magic boy.

511
00:37:29,842 --> 00:37:33,095
And you're nothing without Excalibur.

512
00:37:33,136 --> 00:37:37,140
You're not waiting for someone
to pull it out for you, are you?

513
00:37:37,182 --> 00:37:38,183
How did you know??

514
00:37:38,225 --> 00:37:39,476
Is it true?

515
00:37:54,032 --> 00:37:56,034
Hans, you shouldn't have!

516
00:37:56,076 --> 00:37:58,829
Something sweet for someone sweeter.

517
00:38:01,123 --> 00:38:02,666
This is, this is spectacular!

518
00:38:02,708 --> 00:38:05,335
Awe, it's nothing.
Just let me know what you want,

519
00:38:05,377 --> 00:38:07,838
anytime, for the rest of your life.

520
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:08,631
Do you like fondue?

521
00:38:08,672 --> 00:38:13,969
Behold, carved by the finest jewelers out
of all the jewelers I know.

522
00:38:14,011 --> 00:38:15,220
Which is a lot.

523
00:38:16,597 --> 00:38:17,514
It's pretty.

524
00:38:17,556 --> 00:38:22,019
And it's yours, Miss Shoes.
Yours, in exchange for nothing.

525
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:22,978
Maybe a kiss.

526
00:38:23,020 --> 00:38:26,231
That's really sweet, Jack, but I can't accept it.

527
00:38:26,273 --> 00:38:29,192
I don't want your jewels,
only your good intentions.

528
00:38:29,234 --> 00:38:32,613
My intentions are more than good.
They're super-bon.

529
00:38:32,655 --> 00:38:33,739
Testing, one two.

530
00:38:33,781 --> 00:38:36,659
Testing. No I'm pushing that, you dolt.

531
00:38:36,700 --> 00:38:38,702
Attention, hideous dwarfs!

532
00:38:38,744 --> 00:38:43,498
Is it dwarfs, with a "F", or dwarves, with a "V"?
I want to use whatever's more offensive.

533
00:38:43,540 --> 00:38:45,584
Oh, it's that loser, Prince Average.

534
00:38:45,626 --> 00:38:48,003
Heard that! It's "Ave-voo-RAHJ."

535
00:38:48,045 --> 00:38:49,004
Oh, please.

536
00:38:49,046 --> 00:38:53,091
Inside your amateurish attempt
at a facade of a sham of a travesty

537
00:38:53,133 --> 00:38:57,429
of a veneer of a castle
is a gorgeous wanted criminal.

538
00:38:57,470 --> 00:39:01,934
I hereby command that all of you exit the premises
and surrender post haste!

539
00:39:01,975 --> 00:39:06,438
Fail to comply,
and you will never see these two again.

540
00:39:06,479 --> 00:39:08,273
You have until three...

541
00:39:08,315 --> 00:39:08,899
One...!

542
00:39:11,401 --> 00:39:12,402
Two...!

543
00:39:12,444 --> 00:39:13,779
I lied! Charge!

544
00:39:34,466 --> 00:39:36,009
Am I the person you want?

545
00:39:36,051 --> 00:39:37,845
Yes. Yes, you are.

546
00:39:37,886 --> 00:39:40,430
Though I don't know if you're a person
or a vision of beauty,

547
00:39:40,472 --> 00:39:43,809
some kind of angelic... thing with wings...

548
00:39:43,851 --> 00:39:45,894
angelic wing thing.

549
00:39:45,936 --> 00:39:49,314
I will come with you.
But only after you release my friends.

550
00:39:49,356 --> 00:39:50,691
Do it. Do it!

551
00:39:52,735 --> 00:39:54,236
Now. Here's the good news.

552
00:39:54,277 --> 00:39:58,991
It's my birthday --
and you are going to be the belle of the ball.

553
00:39:59,074 --> 00:40:02,828
The invitation sounds great, really. But...

554
00:40:02,870 --> 00:40:05,163
It wasn't an invitation, more of an order.

555
00:40:05,205 --> 00:40:06,081
Prepare the lady's carriage.

556
00:40:06,123 --> 00:40:08,876
She said she doesn't wanna go, Average.

557
00:40:08,917 --> 00:40:13,839
Ave-voo-rahj. Don't troll me, troll.

558
00:40:13,881 --> 00:40:15,048
So rude!

559
00:40:15,132 --> 00:40:18,468
I couldn't agree more!
Subjects these days. Now, shall we?

560
00:40:27,019 --> 00:40:27,561
Get her!

561
00:40:28,395 --> 00:40:30,230
You hold off the guards,
and I'll get her out of here.

562
00:40:30,272 --> 00:40:33,150
No, I'm faster! You stay here and buy us time.

563
00:40:41,324 --> 00:40:44,578
Here's a thought. Stop fighting...and fight!

564
00:40:45,996 --> 00:40:47,080
What's the plan?

565
00:40:48,081 --> 00:40:49,625
Let's rescue Red Shoes.

566
00:40:49,667 --> 00:40:51,585
Like the old days, guys.

567
00:41:26,620 --> 00:41:27,454
Arthur!

568
00:41:33,418 --> 00:41:35,713
Can we get this over with, they're just dwarfs.

569
00:41:48,225 --> 00:41:50,561
Hey. Did you guys hear something?

570
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:00,362
Come on!

571
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:13,041
Uh oh.

572
00:42:28,140 --> 00:42:30,017
Hi guards, are we taking a break?

573
00:42:30,058 --> 00:42:31,769
Well FYI -

574
00:42:31,810 --> 00:42:34,062
THEY'RE GETTING AWAY!

575
00:42:47,910 --> 00:42:50,871
Who's throwing vegetables? Huh?

576
00:42:55,208 --> 00:42:57,878
Yeah! You just got Merlin'd!

577
00:43:05,886 --> 00:43:06,679
Run!

578
00:43:08,430 --> 00:43:08,889
Jack!

579
00:43:20,067 --> 00:43:20,734
Duck!

580
00:43:25,989 --> 00:43:27,783
I'm so sorry, are you alright?

581
00:43:27,825 --> 00:43:30,243
No, I'm not.

582
00:43:35,874 --> 00:43:38,877
Gentlemen, he surrenders.

583
00:43:38,961 --> 00:43:39,587
What?

584
00:44:09,950 --> 00:44:11,619
Engines, full power!

585
00:44:11,660 --> 00:44:12,285
Shields up!

586
00:44:13,495 --> 00:44:15,205
Turn on the mini-fridge!

587
00:44:34,016 --> 00:44:35,433
Superhero landing!

588
00:44:35,475 --> 00:44:36,434
Hooray for us!

589
00:44:36,476 --> 00:44:38,896
We did it! It was mostly me.

590
00:44:40,355 --> 00:44:41,148
What?

591
00:44:44,902 --> 00:44:46,111
You got to be kidding.

592
00:44:46,153 --> 00:44:48,906
Finally, the big guns. Thank you!

593
00:44:48,989 --> 00:44:49,990
FIRE!

594
00:44:58,081 --> 00:44:59,082
FIRE!

595
00:45:05,255 --> 00:45:06,674
Ooh, close.

596
00:45:06,715 --> 00:45:09,009
The cannonball, not you.

597
00:45:09,051 --> 00:45:12,304
OK Time out, time out! Everyone time out!

598
00:45:12,345 --> 00:45:15,766
You almost blew her up.
And she can't come to my party if you blow her up!

599
00:45:15,808 --> 00:45:17,059
Sorry sir...

600
00:45:17,100 --> 00:45:18,393
All right, time back in.

601
00:45:19,645 --> 00:45:20,688
Surrender, monsters!

602
00:45:20,729 --> 00:45:21,855
No - Wait!

603
00:45:54,387 --> 00:45:55,973
Huh, that's pretty cool.

604
00:46:03,521 --> 00:46:05,482
Everyone inside! And hurry!

605
00:46:07,025 --> 00:46:07,484
WHAAAA!

606
00:46:19,788 --> 00:46:22,165
You messed with the wrong prince!

607
00:46:22,207 --> 00:46:25,002
There's nothing Average about Ave- voo-RAHJ!

608
00:46:25,043 --> 00:46:28,546
I shall return!

609
00:46:28,589 --> 00:46:29,464
On Tuesday.

610
00:46:29,506 --> 00:46:32,843
No, wait, let me check my calendar... Thursday.

611
00:46:32,885 --> 00:46:36,179
I shall return Thursday!

612
00:46:37,556 --> 00:46:38,557
We'll be ready!

613
00:46:38,599 --> 00:46:39,516
And waiting!

614
00:46:39,558 --> 00:46:40,684
Arrivederci!

615
00:46:40,726 --> 00:46:41,644
Chow for now!

616
00:46:41,685 --> 00:46:42,603
Bye, bye!

617
00:46:42,645 --> 00:46:46,148
You just got dwarfed! Is that better?
I think Merlin'd is better.

618
00:47:02,665 --> 00:47:06,877
You should have seen the look on his big,
ugly face when Bunny came running at him.

619
00:47:08,003 --> 00:47:10,422
That's how you see everything, isn't it?

620
00:47:10,463 --> 00:47:11,799
With my eyes?

621
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:14,552
You always talk about what someone looks like.

622
00:47:14,593 --> 00:47:15,844
I do?

623
00:47:15,886 --> 00:47:20,057
I wouldn't say that.
But I can't wait for you to see the real me.

624
00:47:20,098 --> 00:47:22,142
What kind of Merlin is the real you?

625
00:47:22,184 --> 00:47:23,769
You might not believe it,

626
00:47:23,811 --> 00:47:27,565
but the real me is famous, handsome
and even popular.

627
00:47:27,606 --> 00:47:30,818
Not short, stumpy and green.

628
00:47:30,859 --> 00:47:36,699
Yeah, you're short, stumpy and green.
But you're also a wonderful and charming person.

629
00:47:36,740 --> 00:47:42,037
I'm not explaining it right. If you saw the real me,
you'd know exactly what I mean.

630
00:47:42,830 --> 00:47:44,832
I think I can see the real you.

631
00:47:45,332 --> 00:47:48,001
And I like you, just as you are.

632
00:47:50,754 --> 00:47:51,964
That's hilarious.

633
00:47:52,005 --> 00:47:56,384
Here - close your eyes, and imagine the real me.

634
00:47:56,468 --> 00:47:58,679
I guarantee you it'll be different.

635
00:48:00,347 --> 00:48:04,351
I do feel something different.

636
00:48:04,392 --> 00:48:05,352
-- Really?

637
00:48:05,393 --> 00:48:10,315
But eyes opened or closed,
to me you're still Merlin.

638
00:48:11,817 --> 00:48:16,780
Now tell me, who am I to you?

639
00:48:16,822 --> 00:48:23,161
You're a gift.
A gift that'll transform me into someone amazing.

640
00:48:23,203 --> 00:48:25,122
Just like you're amazing.

641
00:48:33,714 --> 00:48:36,800
Actually, I want to show you something, too.

642
00:48:41,597 --> 00:48:42,806
Do you need a hand?

643
00:48:42,848 --> 00:48:46,810
Hold on! Nope. Stand back. I got this.

644
00:48:46,852 --> 00:48:50,272
One, two...Okay, yeah. I need help.

645
00:49:08,373 --> 00:49:11,710
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. Nope.
Thank you though.

646
00:49:17,841 --> 00:49:20,678
You know the weird thing is,
they're super comfortable.

647
00:49:23,346 --> 00:49:26,642
No, I'm just saying, where were you
when the facade was falling?

648
00:49:26,684 --> 00:49:28,811
I mean that was terrifying.

649
00:49:30,688 --> 00:49:31,647
What are you doing here?

650
00:49:33,774 --> 00:49:35,734
I've come for my shoes.

651
00:49:35,776 --> 00:49:40,614
Well, I had them. I mean, I saw them.
But those, those dwarfs.

652
00:49:40,656 --> 00:49:42,908
It's dwarves. With a "v." So you failed?

653
00:49:43,366 --> 00:49:45,077
I did not fail.

654
00:49:45,118 --> 00:49:47,580
I took a time-out.

655
00:49:47,621 --> 00:49:49,665
Yeah, this is a calculated time- out,

656
00:49:49,707 --> 00:49:51,875
I'm going to return on Thursday,
we all penciled it in.

657
00:49:51,917 --> 00:49:53,085
Silence!

658
00:49:53,126 --> 00:49:54,211
Have a bite.

659
00:49:55,253 --> 00:49:56,797
For strength.

660
00:49:57,339 --> 00:50:01,677
Apples. The most suspicious of fruits.

661
00:50:01,719 --> 00:50:04,512
I don't have much time, Prince.

662
00:50:04,555 --> 00:50:08,851
You could still have the best birthday ever.

663
00:50:08,892 --> 00:50:16,900
But remember what's bad for me,
will be very bad for you.

664
00:50:22,823 --> 00:50:23,616
She is gone...

665
00:50:25,158 --> 00:50:27,494
Ah, what's the worst that could happen?

666
00:50:31,539 --> 00:50:32,415
It's kinda sweet...

667
00:50:48,599 --> 00:50:49,683
Don't move.

668
00:50:49,767 --> 00:50:50,601
Okay.

669
00:50:50,643 --> 00:50:52,645
Pino, Noki, Kio - show us what you got!

670
00:50:52,686 --> 00:50:53,604
Okey-dokey!

671
00:50:53,646 --> 00:50:54,396
Here we go!

672
00:50:54,479 --> 00:50:55,606
Our pleasure!

673
00:51:02,696 --> 00:51:06,491
Keep going, little to the left. right there.

674
00:51:23,133 --> 00:51:24,802
Now that looks like a real home.

675
00:51:24,843 --> 00:51:27,012
Yeah. I could get used to that.

676
00:51:27,054 --> 00:51:28,263
Nu-uh. I cannot.

677
00:51:32,142 --> 00:51:35,145
It's a perfect copy of my drawing! That's incredible!

678
00:51:36,479 --> 00:51:37,690
Let me try.

679
00:51:37,731 --> 00:51:41,401
Wow. This will definitely make it easier
to find your dad.

680
00:51:41,443 --> 00:51:43,612
Unfortunately, this thing ain't flying.

681
00:51:43,654 --> 00:51:44,613
It's grounded.

682
00:51:44,655 --> 00:51:45,573
Why does it need to fly?

683
00:51:45,614 --> 00:51:48,450
The posters are no good
if we can't distribute them fast.

684
00:51:48,491 --> 00:51:52,705
Guys, thank you so much
for everything you're doing for me.

685
00:52:16,061 --> 00:52:17,062
Hi~

686
00:52:40,586 --> 00:52:42,087
Wow! look at that!

687
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:53,223
Wow.

688
00:53:04,401 --> 00:53:05,653
opening doors!

689
00:53:21,376 --> 00:53:25,338
You know, merlin?
I feel so lucky that I've meet you.

690
00:53:25,380 --> 00:53:27,675
I feel the same way!

691
00:53:27,716 --> 00:53:30,969
I feel like anything is possible!

692
00:53:47,277 --> 00:53:49,321
Merlin! watch out!

693
00:54:00,415 --> 00:54:01,792
Merlin.

694
00:54:03,627 --> 00:54:04,712
Merlin.

695
00:54:06,088 --> 00:54:06,504
Merlin!

696
00:54:07,339 --> 00:54:09,007
everything OK?

697
00:54:09,549 --> 00:54:11,552
Of course, sure!

698
00:54:11,594 --> 00:54:12,845
Nothing to be embarrassed about.

699
00:54:12,886 --> 00:54:17,099
So why are we even talking about
that when we should be going...

700
00:54:17,140 --> 00:54:18,058
this direction.

701
00:54:18,100 --> 00:54:19,184
Hey, wait!

702
00:54:23,021 --> 00:54:25,899
So, about these magic shoes.

703
00:54:25,941 --> 00:54:27,317
Are those still bothering you?

704
00:54:27,359 --> 00:54:29,319
What kind of magic do those shoes have?

705
00:54:29,695 --> 00:54:32,823
Well...How do I put this?

706
00:54:32,865 --> 00:54:36,827
Merlin, I used to be strong. Really strong.

707
00:54:36,869 --> 00:54:39,537
And, I was always proud of that.

708
00:54:39,622 --> 00:54:44,752
But the shoes' magic, um,
it made me a little dainty.

709
00:54:44,793 --> 00:54:45,543
Sorry to hear.

710
00:54:45,586 --> 00:54:49,798
The shoes made me lose a little bit of weight.

711
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:51,216
Could be worse.

712
00:54:51,258 --> 00:54:55,095
Ok, a lot of weight.

713
00:54:55,137 --> 00:54:56,221
Ah.

714
00:54:56,263 --> 00:55:00,308
Well, I know what it's like to look different
on the outside from what you feel on the inside.

715
00:55:04,897 --> 00:55:09,026
Merlin, I'd like to do give you a token
of my appreciation.

716
00:55:10,527 --> 00:55:12,613
Oh, here. Hand me one of your spells.

717
00:55:12,655 --> 00:55:13,572
Why?

718
00:55:13,614 --> 00:55:16,033
Oh come on, I'm not going to zap you.

719
00:55:17,159 --> 00:55:17,993
Give me a sec.

720
00:55:30,714 --> 00:55:34,301
There. Consider it your good luck charm.

721
00:55:37,888 --> 00:55:39,890
Thank you.

722
00:55:45,688 --> 00:55:52,069
Merlin, do you think we'd be happier
if we were our old selves again?

723
00:55:52,110 --> 00:55:55,072
Yep. Yep, yep, definitely we would.

724
00:55:55,113 --> 00:56:03,872
I don't know. I like how we are.
Right here, just, right now.

725
00:56:03,914 --> 00:56:07,417
Even if I'm an ugly green monster?

726
00:56:09,002 --> 00:56:12,590
I don't care about your height
or what color you are

727
00:56:13,506 --> 00:56:17,219
that's the way you feel about me, right?

728
00:56:17,260 --> 00:56:20,347
Yes, of course! I mean, duh.

729
00:56:22,099 --> 00:56:25,352
I think we're both just trapped
under the same spell.

730
00:56:42,160 --> 00:56:48,041
Wait. Keep your eyes closed.
Don't open them until I say.

731
00:56:48,083 --> 00:56:53,505
When you open your eyes,
there will be a handsome man in front of you.

732
00:56:53,546 --> 00:56:57,092
Someone worthy of you.
Someone you'd be proud to be seen with.

733
00:56:58,135 --> 00:56:59,302
I think you're right.

734
00:56:59,344 --> 00:57:02,264
Ready, and...

735
00:57:02,305 --> 00:57:04,808
It's such a good day to break a curse.

736
00:57:07,895 --> 00:57:08,395
Now!

737
00:57:09,479 --> 00:57:15,527
Tada! You just got Merlin'd! Ha-ha!
What do you think?

738
00:57:15,569 --> 00:57:18,781
Mission impossibly handsome, right?

739
00:57:20,574 --> 00:57:24,077
It's okay. I know this is a lot to take in.

740
00:57:24,119 --> 00:57:27,164
But you can let your happiness flag fly.

741
00:57:27,205 --> 00:57:30,709
This. This. Is the real me.

742
00:57:31,794 --> 00:57:32,878
Ha Ha it's stupid.

743
00:57:32,920 --> 00:57:39,092
What? Wait a minute.
My hands are still green sausages.

744
00:57:40,093 --> 00:57:42,888
No. I look the same.

745
00:57:42,930 --> 00:57:45,182
Yes. Impossibly handsome.

746
00:57:45,223 --> 00:57:47,685
This doesn't make sense.

747
00:57:47,726 --> 00:57:50,688
You're the most beautiful woman in the world!
Why do I look the same?

748
00:57:50,729 --> 00:57:52,815
What are you talking about, Merlin?

749
00:57:52,856 --> 00:57:54,399
Do I need a longer kiss?

750
00:57:54,441 --> 00:57:55,651
Two kisses?

751
00:57:56,610 --> 00:57:58,528
Let's try again.

752
00:57:58,571 --> 00:58:01,198
Um, you're not making any sense.

753
00:58:10,123 --> 00:58:10,874
Hurry!

754
00:58:13,376 --> 00:58:14,127
What is that?!

755
00:58:14,502 --> 00:58:16,797
This kingdom has a serious monster problem!

756
00:58:33,063 --> 00:58:33,731
You all right?

757
00:58:33,772 --> 00:58:35,566
No, I'm not.

758
00:58:44,157 --> 00:58:44,658
Thank you.

759
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:45,618
Pleasure my lady.

760
00:58:46,952 --> 00:58:47,369
Whoa!

761
00:58:48,411 --> 00:58:49,162
Watch out!

762
00:59:06,096 --> 00:59:07,430
Ha ha. Yes!

763
00:59:07,681 --> 00:59:08,140
What?

764
00:59:15,022 --> 00:59:17,650
What do they want?! Besides smashing us?

765
00:59:17,691 --> 00:59:18,316
I don't know!

766
00:59:27,492 --> 00:59:29,286
The old me would have nailed that!

767
00:59:37,753 --> 00:59:39,129
You just got Merlin'd!

768
00:59:49,848 --> 00:59:50,473
Hurry!

769
01:00:06,406 --> 01:00:08,075
Red, close your eyes.

770
01:00:08,116 --> 01:00:09,785
Um, this is no time for kissing, Merlin!

771
01:00:09,827 --> 01:00:11,912
Just trust me. Close your eyes.

772
01:00:13,121 --> 01:00:14,748
Please! Close them!

773
01:00:19,461 --> 01:00:20,838
That was too close.

774
01:00:21,714 --> 01:00:23,215
Don't look at me.

775
01:00:23,256 --> 01:00:25,383
You see that tree on the other side of the bridge?

776
01:00:25,425 --> 01:00:25,884
Yeah.

777
01:00:25,926 --> 01:00:29,054
On my signal, run towards it as fast as you can.

778
01:00:29,096 --> 01:00:30,472
No, I can't leave you here!

779
01:00:30,513 --> 01:00:33,767
You have to. And don't look back, okay?

780
01:00:33,851 --> 01:00:36,394
Look right at that tree until I say it's safe.

781
01:00:36,436 --> 01:00:38,105
Promise you won't look.

782
01:00:38,146 --> 01:00:40,608
Um, okay. I promise.

783
01:00:41,191 --> 01:00:41,692
Now!

784
01:01:13,766 --> 01:01:14,850
What's that?

785
01:01:14,892 --> 01:01:17,019
You just got Merlin'd! Yes you did.

786
01:01:46,214 --> 01:01:47,800
Hey, block-head!

787
01:01:48,884 --> 01:01:50,844
Hey block-head bear!

788
01:01:50,886 --> 01:01:53,806
You're even more
of a block-head than Prince Average!

789
01:01:56,266 --> 01:01:58,435
Ave-voo-rahj!

790
01:01:59,061 --> 01:02:00,228
Prince Average?

791
01:02:16,369 --> 01:02:17,996
You just got Merlin'd.

792
01:02:21,750 --> 01:02:23,085
Take a look, Red Shoes.

793
01:02:23,586 --> 01:02:24,169
Merlin!

794
01:02:24,252 --> 01:02:26,546
I have triumphantly saved the day!

795
01:02:27,673 --> 01:02:28,591
Merlin! No!

796
01:02:31,093 --> 01:02:31,760
No!

797
01:02:31,802 --> 01:02:32,385
Merlin!

798
01:03:43,331 --> 01:03:44,792
Snow White?

799
01:03:54,552 --> 01:03:59,222
Snow White?
The thief was Snow White this whole time?!

800
01:03:59,264 --> 01:04:02,810
Interesting. She could remove the shoes.

801
01:04:04,603 --> 01:04:07,022
You're going after her yourself?

802
01:04:07,064 --> 01:04:08,857
What? Were you going to go?

803
01:04:08,899 --> 01:04:11,694
I get it. I don't have legs.

804
01:04:14,780 --> 01:04:19,910
So. Here I am. Well, the real me.

805
01:04:21,579 --> 01:04:23,413
I bet you're disappointed, huh?

806
01:04:23,455 --> 01:04:27,042
You're the girl from Golden Goose Avenue.
Red Shoes!

807
01:04:27,084 --> 01:04:30,337
That's not my name. It's Snow White.

808
01:04:30,378 --> 01:04:33,048
Princess Snow White? So your father is --

809
01:04:33,090 --> 01:04:35,801
King White, yeah.

810
01:04:35,843 --> 01:04:42,349
By the time I figured out his new wife Regina
was a witch, he'd already disappeared.

811
01:04:42,390 --> 01:04:48,689
And the monsters who attacked us were sent
by my stepmother to get these shoes.

812
01:04:50,608 --> 01:04:53,526
I guess being beautiful is really worth
that much to her...

813
01:04:53,569 --> 01:04:56,780
Have you thought about just giving them back?

814
01:04:57,781 --> 01:04:59,032
And give up their magic?

815
01:05:00,618 --> 01:05:04,246
If I'd given up their magic you wouldn't have
helped me find my father, would you?

816
01:05:05,413 --> 01:05:06,414
Would you?

817
01:05:10,418 --> 01:05:12,545
I thought we were both under the same spell,

818
01:05:14,256 --> 01:05:17,801
but I see now that, I was wrong.

819
01:05:17,843 --> 01:05:23,431
Listen, I can't get into all the details,
but I'm under a curse too.

820
01:05:23,473 --> 01:05:25,183
You still don't get it, Merlin.

821
01:05:26,727 --> 01:05:28,896
I'm not talking about our curses,

822
01:05:30,063 --> 01:05:35,527
Merlin, I'm talking about the kind
of spell you never want to break.

823
01:06:24,910 --> 01:06:26,912
He likes you more than he likes me.

824
01:06:59,277 --> 01:07:02,573
What would have happened if she had
taken off her shoes that day in the barn?

825
01:07:02,615 --> 01:07:03,907
You think that's important?

826
01:07:06,660 --> 01:07:11,582
I just wonder what I would have done
if I had seen the real Snow White.

827
01:07:11,624 --> 01:07:15,586
Seriously?
It's still all about appearance for you.

828
01:07:15,628 --> 01:07:18,296
No! Not exactly.

829
01:07:19,172 --> 01:07:22,425
But I can't live looking like you
for the rest of my life!

830
01:07:22,467 --> 01:07:24,469
Kind of proving my point, other me.

831
01:07:24,511 --> 01:07:26,930
Alright, let's try this--

832
01:07:26,972 --> 01:07:29,683
who do you like more, Snow White or Red Shoes?

833
01:07:29,767 --> 01:07:32,019
Easy! It's Red Shoes.

834
01:07:32,060 --> 01:07:34,730
Now, which of us do you think
Red Shoes likes more?

835
01:07:34,772 --> 01:07:36,106
Easy! It's-- me,

836
01:07:38,108 --> 01:07:43,864
wait, no, it's you?

837
01:08:20,233 --> 01:08:25,823
You're a gift. A gift that'll transform me
into someone amazing.

838
01:08:46,844 --> 01:08:50,763
Well, I know what it's like to look different
on the outside from what you feel on the inside.

839
01:09:10,658 --> 01:09:11,577
look at that!

840
01:09:16,624 --> 01:09:19,667
The shoes. You're wearing them?

841
01:09:19,710 --> 01:09:21,253
I thought you left.

842
01:09:21,293 --> 01:09:23,005
You should take them off again.

843
01:09:28,260 --> 01:09:29,970
I can't.

844
01:09:30,012 --> 01:09:33,223
Ugh, you just had to make things complicated.

845
01:09:34,016 --> 01:09:35,808
Maybe this will help.

846
01:09:35,851 --> 01:09:38,270
Eat the apple, and they'll slide right off.

847
01:09:38,310 --> 01:09:39,146
Where did you get that?

848
01:09:39,186 --> 01:09:42,815
I want to help you, Snow White. Please.

849
01:09:49,782 --> 01:09:50,490
Red Shoes?

850
01:09:51,323 --> 01:09:51,949
Merlin?

851
01:09:53,200 --> 01:09:54,201
Merlin??

852
01:09:57,289 --> 01:09:59,416
What terrible timing you have.

853
01:10:01,669 --> 01:10:04,504
Uggh, we're going to have to do this the hard way.

854
01:10:05,087 --> 01:10:06,006
Regina?

855
01:10:08,466 --> 01:10:12,971
Aw. Such a tender family reunion.

856
01:10:13,013 --> 01:10:14,848
So sad we can't stay.

857
01:10:15,974 --> 01:10:17,017
Red Shoes!

858
01:10:19,352 --> 01:10:21,521
C'mon. Let's go, long ears!

859
01:10:21,564 --> 01:10:23,106
Hey! Wait for us!

860
01:10:23,148 --> 01:10:25,108
How about you go back and get the others.

861
01:10:25,150 --> 01:10:27,277
And make lots of copies of this.

862
01:10:27,736 --> 01:10:28,403
Let's go!

863
01:10:31,281 --> 01:10:32,741
We can do this!

864
01:10:35,994 --> 01:10:38,581
Your power, my lady, it has drained you.

865
01:10:38,622 --> 01:10:42,375
You think? I don't need you tell me how I look.

866
01:10:42,417 --> 01:10:47,923
I'm a mirror. It's what I do?
M-I-R- O-R. I can't spell.

867
01:10:47,965 --> 01:10:48,423
Enough!

868
01:10:50,133 --> 01:10:54,555
Bind her. It's snack time.

869
01:10:58,225 --> 01:11:00,268
How can you sleep-eat at a time like this?

870
01:11:02,020 --> 01:11:04,690
I'm not supposed to talk when I have this on,

871
01:11:04,732 --> 01:11:08,068
but I gotta ask - do you think they've kissed yet?

872
01:11:08,110 --> 01:11:12,239
I hope so. Because it'll feel better
to punch Merlin when he's pretty.

873
01:11:13,323 --> 01:11:16,827
We've been waiting forever! Where have you --

874
01:11:16,869 --> 01:11:17,786
Did you break the curse, yet?

875
01:11:17,828 --> 01:11:19,580
Ah, Merlin - are you hungry?

876
01:11:19,622 --> 01:11:20,372
Those are bears.

877
01:11:20,413 --> 01:11:26,003
Uh, hi. This is from Merlin.

878
01:11:42,519 --> 01:11:44,563
Wow. This is so cool.

879
01:11:48,692 --> 01:11:50,277
Okay, sword.

880
01:11:50,318 --> 01:11:54,907
If you think you've humiliated,
embarrassed and otherwise frustrated me...

881
01:11:55,532 --> 01:11:57,409
You're right.

882
01:11:57,492 --> 01:12:01,079
But that ends now!

883
01:12:10,714 --> 01:12:12,758
Oh, please end this.

884
01:12:24,394 --> 01:12:28,481
Hey! Wait! you are running the wrong way!

885
01:12:28,523 --> 01:12:29,858
The castle is over there!

886
01:12:45,290 --> 01:12:47,334
Uh, "sit."

887
01:12:59,262 --> 01:13:03,350
Eat this, darling, and you'll get your freedom.

888
01:13:03,391 --> 01:13:04,476
Where's my father?

889
01:13:04,517 --> 01:13:09,648
Uggh. Royal, loyal little girl,
pining for her papa.

890
01:13:09,732 --> 01:13:14,236
This is getting a little boring.
So I need you to take a bite, and I'll tell you.

891
01:13:14,277 --> 01:13:17,322
I won't let you win. You've torn apart my family,

892
01:13:17,364 --> 01:13:19,282
and you will not get away with it, Regina.

893
01:13:20,618 --> 01:13:23,536
Ooh, so scared, Snow.

894
01:13:23,579 --> 01:13:26,749
Very well. A different approach, then.

895
01:13:35,382 --> 01:13:36,008
Merlin!

896
01:13:37,050 --> 01:13:38,927
Eat the apple or watch him die.

897
01:13:39,011 --> 01:13:40,095
That's your choice.

898
01:13:40,137 --> 01:13:46,727
Red Shoes! Don't do it!

899
01:13:46,769 --> 01:13:49,187
Promise to me you'll let him go.

900
01:13:49,229 --> 01:13:52,440
Oh absolutely. When the third bell chimes,

901
01:13:52,482 --> 01:13:55,360
everything will be just like it used to be.

902
01:13:55,443 --> 01:13:57,362
Red Shoes, don't do it! No!

903
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:01,366
Save my papa for me.

904
01:14:28,811 --> 01:14:33,273
The Legendary handsome Merlin,
fearless rescuer of princesses...

905
01:14:33,315 --> 01:14:41,448
...sitting in a tree. Not getting K-I-S-I-N-G'd!
Burn! I can't spell.

906
01:14:43,617 --> 01:14:47,079
You don't have to do this.
Just take the shoes and let us go!

907
01:14:47,120 --> 01:14:50,583
Ugh, I wish! They're made of pure magic apple --

908
01:14:50,624 --> 01:14:53,836
the fruit of temptation and want.
They feed on your desires.

909
01:14:53,919 --> 01:14:58,173
And once they give you what you desire,
the bond is permanent.

910
01:14:58,215 --> 01:15:00,508
That's not true. She took them off in the river.

911
01:15:00,551 --> 01:15:02,553
That doesn't make any sense.

912
01:15:02,595 --> 01:15:07,057
How could she possibly want to save you
more than she wanted to be beautiful?

913
01:15:07,099 --> 01:15:09,309
What did you do to her?

914
01:15:09,351 --> 01:15:11,478
Did you cast a spell?

915
01:15:13,480 --> 01:15:15,315
What's going to happen to her?

916
01:15:15,357 --> 01:15:20,237
Well, once she eats the apple,
its magic will turn her into a magic apple tree.

917
01:15:20,278 --> 01:15:23,240
Gong! First bell sounds. Very dramatic.

918
01:15:23,281 --> 01:15:26,034
The tree bears fruit at the second bell.

919
01:15:26,076 --> 01:15:30,581
Gong! Excitement mounts!
The morning sun touches the fruit,

920
01:15:30,623 --> 01:15:33,041
turning it into a new pair of red shoes.

921
01:15:33,083 --> 01:15:36,003
Gong number three! The circle of life!

922
01:15:36,044 --> 01:15:37,420
And then what?

923
01:15:37,462 --> 01:15:42,384
Regina will be the most beautiful person
in the kingdom. Forever.

924
01:15:42,425 --> 01:15:45,137
I don't care about her! What about Snow White?

925
01:15:45,220 --> 01:15:49,683
The tree withers and dies. And so does Snow White.

926
01:15:49,725 --> 01:15:51,476
No!

927
01:15:51,518 --> 01:15:57,900
Yas! Oh! I'm rotting! I'm dying.

928
01:16:14,708 --> 01:16:17,586
Why don't you come back and play.

929
01:16:24,009 --> 01:16:25,343
Not so fast.

930
01:16:34,728 --> 01:16:35,896
It's gonna hurt.

931
01:16:39,567 --> 01:16:42,527
Oh yeah! Stretch it out.

932
01:16:54,247 --> 01:16:55,040
Uh oh.

933
01:17:00,003 --> 01:17:01,088
Smoke! Smoke!

934
01:17:01,171 --> 01:17:03,465
We're here, mate. Are you OK?

935
01:17:03,506 --> 01:17:05,008
Yeah

936
01:17:05,050 --> 01:17:10,305
I never thought I'd say this,
but I'm so glad to be chubby and green again.

937
01:17:11,181 --> 01:17:15,603
Seven to one, I like those odds. Let's go.

938
01:17:17,730 --> 01:17:19,690
We like those odds even better.

939
01:17:22,359 --> 01:17:23,944
Are you up to this, muchacho?

940
01:17:23,986 --> 01:17:27,656
Wow. You finally pulled out Excalibur!

941
01:17:27,698 --> 01:17:32,035
Uh huh. Yeah, yeah, I did it,
that's exactly how it went down.

942
01:17:32,119 --> 01:17:34,204
Here you go, Merlin, you're gonna need these.

943
01:17:34,246 --> 01:17:35,664
Thanks.

944
01:17:41,128 --> 01:17:43,130
Here comes the sun.

945
01:17:43,672 --> 01:17:45,548
Now let's all get dwarfed!

946
01:17:49,887 --> 01:17:54,057
This is where your fairy tale ends, trolls!

947
01:17:58,562 --> 01:17:59,521
You missed.

948
01:18:36,642 --> 01:18:38,268
Au revoir, mirror!

949
01:18:53,408 --> 01:18:54,534
Finally..!

950
01:19:03,293 --> 01:19:05,545
It's a good day to break a curse!

951
01:19:07,715 --> 01:19:09,424
...Eternal beauty!

952
01:19:23,271 --> 01:19:25,733
I'm sorry, Snow White.

953
01:19:28,694 --> 01:19:32,405
Noo!

954
01:19:58,932 --> 01:20:01,935
Extraordinary no more carrots for me.

955
01:20:07,524 --> 01:20:08,441
Woah!

956
01:20:08,483 --> 01:20:09,526
We're back!

957
01:20:09,568 --> 01:20:10,360
Yippee!

958
01:20:20,746 --> 01:20:21,329
Papa!

959
01:20:31,840 --> 01:20:33,258
Snow White!

960
01:20:35,510 --> 01:20:36,929
Oh, Papa!

961
01:20:36,970 --> 01:20:37,638
Snow!

962
01:20:42,976 --> 01:20:43,393
Wait.

963
01:20:44,269 --> 01:20:45,604
Where's Merlin?

964
01:20:45,646 --> 01:20:47,522
I'm so sorry.

965
01:20:47,565 --> 01:20:51,526
He sacrificed himself to stop Regina.

966
01:20:52,235 --> 01:20:53,571
Merlin, no!

967
01:20:56,865 --> 01:20:58,325
Merlin!

968
01:21:58,927 --> 01:22:00,262
I thought you were gone.

969
01:22:01,639 --> 01:22:05,643
You're the most beautiful woman in the world.

970
01:22:07,770 --> 01:22:12,858
Whether my eyes are open or closed.

971
01:22:24,452 --> 01:22:25,245
No...

972
01:22:42,930 --> 01:22:44,181
I got Merlin'd.

973
01:23:09,915 --> 01:23:11,499
You're Prince Merlin.

974
01:23:19,257 --> 01:23:25,388
Yeah. That Merlin.
The one who's not really your type.

975
01:23:29,017 --> 01:23:31,144
I kinda liked the short and green Merlin.

976
01:23:34,106 --> 01:23:36,191
But I'm still that Merlin inside.

977
01:23:37,525 --> 01:23:40,320
Yes. Yes you are.

978
01:23:47,828 --> 01:23:48,787
Yay!

979
01:23:48,829 --> 01:23:50,372
Yes!

980
01:23:50,413 --> 01:23:52,625
Hooray!

981
01:23:52,750 --> 01:23:53,375
Nice!

982
01:23:58,672 --> 01:24:00,507
Any idea who that girl is?

983
01:26:26,654 --> 01:26:27,362
Not again.

984
01:26:38,705 --> 01:26:43,705
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org
